Quick Gotchas

Pipeline Push Fails: GitHub Actions needs your Docker credentials (saved in GitHub Secrets) to push the image.

Data Wipes on Restart: The database is a temporary HashMap. If the app or pod restarts, users/OTPs are deleted.

K8s Needs a Host: kubectl apply won't work unless you have a local cluster running (like Minikube or Docker Desktop).

Required Tools: Ensure Java 17, Maven, Docker, and Git are actually installed on the machine.

🗺️ 4-Step Execution Plan

Code First: Run mvn spring-boot:run locally. Test that the OTP works.

Docker Second: Run docker build and docker run locally. Make sure the container works.

K8s Third: Start your local cluster, run kubectl apply, and check if the pods spin up.

Automate Last: Push the working code to GitHub to trigger the CI/CD pipeline.
